Reasoning: The paper deals with machine learning classification models and provides lower bounds on the minimax expected excess risk. This falls under the domain of machine learning and statistical learning theory, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.ST (Statistics). The paper also uses binomial distributions and voting procedures, which are related to data structures and algorithms, covered by the sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of learning algorithms, which is related to artificial intelligence, covered by the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
